      <div class="layout__item layout__item--body">
        <h2><b>Nicholas Thorne</b></h2>

        <p>
          Nick’s first acting role came to him at age 10, when his primary
          school chose to put on a play about the Amazon rain forest. On hearing
          the headmaster ask whom amongst the class might like to play the lead
          role of Tanok, Nick’s hand eagerly shot into the air, and he insisted
          to the teacher that he would “be a GREAT Tanok”. Possibly due to him
          being the only person who raised their hand, Nick successfully landed
          the part, and a love of acting was born.
        </p>
        <p>

          Since that fateful day, Nick has spent over two decades acting in
          plays, musicals, short films, television and, for a few years, as a
          scarer-of-tourists in the Edinburgh Dungeon. He is also an
          accomplished pianist, and can often be found tinkling out a tune in
          Edinburgh Waverley train station. His favourite things include comedy,
          chess, skiing, and going for walks with his wife (Fiona) and their
          little dog (Shy).
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="layout">
