      <div class="layout__item layout__item--body">
        <h2><b>Kirsty Eila McIntyre</b></h2>

        <p>
          Kirsty Eila McIntyre is an award winning actress and musician from
          Edinburgh. Theatre acting credits include; Castle Lennox (Royal Lyceum
          Theatre Company & Lung Ha, winner of Best Ensemble 2023 at the CATS),
          The Myth of the Singular Moment (Jim Harbourne & Tortoise in a
          Nutshell, winner of the Summerhall Award 2018), Little by Little Field
          (Curious Seed), Glory On Earth (Royal Lyceum Theatre Company), The
          Arrival (Solar Bear), Deliverance (Brite Theater & Vanishing Point),
          Bench on the Road (Charioteer Theatre Company) Audio work includes;
          several audio books, and voices for the theatre shows Childminder
          (Brite Theater), Arthropoda (Paper Doll Militia) and Mrs Barbour's
          Daughters (Tron Theatre). Film & TV credits include; The Last Bus
          (Hurricane Films), Project Unicorn (BBC Scotland/Studio Something) and
          Are We Born to Fear? (BBC Ideas/Shakehaus) She regularly helps to
          develop new work for the stage and has performed in many rehearsed
          readings including for The Real William Shakespeare, as Told by
          Christopher Marlowe. She is thrilled to be performing in the full
          production of this brilliant new play.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="layout">
